article.headline: Dayton 66, Xavier 62
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Norman Plummer scored 15 points, including Dayton's final five in the last 57 seconds, to lead the Flyers to a 66-62 win over Xavier on Tuesday night. Dayton (13-14, 5-8 Atlantic 10) won despite shooting 38 percent in the first half and 42 percent for the game. The Musketeers (16-8, 7-6) tied it at 56 on a 3-pointer from Josh Duncan with 4:26 left. But Brian Roberts answered with a jumper to give the Flyers the lead for good. Dayton then held Xavier scoreless for more than 3 minutes. Roberts finished with 14 points, and Charles Little added 12 for the Flyers, who scored 18 points off turnovers. Duncan finished with 18 points for the Musketeers. Justin Doellman added 12 points and Stanley Burrell had 11.
